#: .\material.json
msgid "bismuth shot"
msgid_plural "bismoth shots"
msgstr[0] "鉍彈丸"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'bismuth shot', 'str_pl': 'bismoth shots'}
#: .\material.json
msgid ""
"An environmentally friendly bismuth alloy bird shot that is lead free and "
"pollution free. A small amount of tin is added to make it hard to break, but"
" it may be used as a substitute for bismuth."
msgstr "一種環保的鉍合金鳥彈，無鉛無汙染。添加少量錫使其不易碎裂，但可作為鉍的替代品使用。"

#: .\material.json
msgid "penny"
msgid_plural "pennies"
msgstr[0] "便士"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'penny', 'str_pl': 'pennies'}
#: .\material.json
msgid ""
"Commonly known as pennies, it is the smallest denomination currency of the "
"United States. Only zinc in the copper plating can be melted and taken out "
"by heating with a lighter."
msgstr "俗稱便士，是美國最小面額的貨幣。只有銅鍍層中的鋅可以通過打火機加熱熔化取出。"

#: .\material.json
msgid "magnesium ribbon"
msgid_plural "magnesium ribbons"
msgstr[0] "鎂帶"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'magnesium ribbon', 'str_pl': 'magnesium
#. ribbons'}
#: .\material.json
msgid ""
"It is magnesium formed into a ribbon shape. It can be used for chemical "
"experiments and field ignition aids, as well as for the production of some "
"ammunition and explosives."
msgstr "這是成型為帶狀的鎂。可用於化學實驗和野外點火輔助，以及生產某些彈藥和爆炸物。"

#: .\modinfo.json
msgid "Metal materials"
msgstr "金屬材料"

#. ~ Description for Metal materials
#: .\modinfo.json
msgid "Add items that can be converted to difficult to obtain metal material."
msgstr "添加可轉化為難以獲取的金屬材料的物品。"
